						               													<description>In In Business, players have to trade goods from one continent to the other. Starting off with a loan from the bank, players have to earn money to pay back the loan and finally make a profit. The first player to own a certain amount of money (depending on the number of players) wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In order to do so, players have to make the most profitable bargains by buying cheap and sell expensive. Each country has its own prizes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game each player gets a goal-card, which shows:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The type of good which have to be traded&amp;#10;     Purchase area&amp;#10;     Sell area&amp;#10;     Purchase and sell prizes&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players move along the board by rolling two dice. For each continent they can choose whether to walk the long- or short route.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game, players can get additional goals, loose or win money at the stock market, or get additional smaller bonuses or losses. Also players can lose their cargo by a casualty during transport, unless their goods are ensured.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The additional rules for experienced players involve a more extensive stock market.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
